    <div id="hello">
        <center><h2>Tribute to Virat Kohli</h2></center>
        <P>Virat Kohli, born on November 5, 1988, in Delhi, India, is not just a cricketer but an icon of modern cricket. His journey from a young aspiring player to one of the greatest batsmen of all time is a testament to his hard work, dedication, and passion for the game.</P>
        <center><h2>Early Life and Career</h2></center>
        <P>From an early age, Kohli displayed an extraordinary talent for cricket. His cricketing journey began in the streets of Delhi, where he honed his skills. He rose through the ranks quickly, making his debut for the Indian national team in 2008. His aggressive playing style and impressive technique caught the attention of fans and critics alike.</P>
        <center><h2>Records and Achievements</h2></center>
        <h4>Virat Kohli’s career is adorned with numerous records and accolades:</h4>
        <P>Most Runs in a Calendar Year: Kohli has achieved the remarkable feat of scoring the most runs in a calendar year multiple times, showcasing his consistency and dominance.
            - Fastest to 8,000, 9,000, 10,000, 11,000 Runs: Kohli holds records for being the fastest to reach these milestones in One Day Internationals (ODIs).
            - International Centuries: He has accumulated over 80 international centuries, reflecting his exceptional skill and temperament.
            - Captaincy: Under his captaincy, India achieved significant victories, including a historic Test series win in Australia in 2018-2019.</P>
        <center><h2>Playing Style and Contributions</h2></center>
        <p>Kohli is known for his aggressive batting, remarkable fitness, and exceptional technique. His ability to chase down challenging targets and his dominance in all formats of the game make him a formidable player. His contributions extend beyond the field; he is also recognized for his philanthropy and efforts to promote fitness and sportsmanship.</p>
        <center><h2>Philanthropy and Personal Life</h2></center>    
        <p>Off the field, Virat Kohli is equally inspiring. He is actively involved in charitable work through the Virat Kohli Foundation, which supports various causes including child welfare and education. His commitment to giving back to society exemplifies his character and values.

            Kohli’s personal life, including his marriage to actress Anushka Sharma and their journey as parents, has garnered significant media attention, but he continues to remain focused on his professional and philanthropic goals.
            
            </p>
        <center><h2>Legacy</h2></center>
        <p>
            Virat Kohli’s impact on cricket is profound. His dedication, skill, and leadership have set new standards in the sport. He is not only admired for his records but also for his relentless pursuit of excellence and his role as a role model for aspiring cricketers around the world.

As Virat Kohli continues to contribute to cricket and beyond, his legacy as one of the greatest cricketers of all time is firmly established.

        </p>
        <center><h2>Quotes and Tributes</h2></center>
        <p>“Virat is a phenomenon. His passion for the game, his work ethic, and his extraordinary skills make him one of the best batsmen of this era.” – [Famous Cricketer/Commentator]
           <br>
         Watching Kohli play is like watching poetry in motion. He’s a master of the game and a true inspiration to all sports enthusiasts.” – [Sports Journalist]
            </p>
